#!/usr/bin/perl

use 5.010;
use strict;
use warnings;

use Perinci::CmdLine;

our $VERSION = '0.03'; # VERSION

Perinci::CmdLine->new(url=>'/Media/Info/get_media_info')->run;

1;
# ABSTRACT: Return information about a media file/URL
# PODNAME: media-file

__END__

=pod

=encoding utf-8

=head1 NAME

media-file - Return information about a media file/URL

=head1 VERSION

version 0.03

=head1 SYNOPSIS

 % media-file /home/steven/celine.mp4

=head1 DESCRIPTION

This is a command-line interface for the C<get_media_info> function in
L<Media::Info>.

=head1 HOMEPAGE

Please visit the project's homepage at L<https://metacpan.org/release/Media-Info>.

=head1 SOURCE

Source repository is at L<https://github.com/sharyanto/perl-Media-Info>.

=head1 BUGS

Please report any bugs or feature requests on the bugtracker website
http://rt.cpan.org/Public/Dist/Display.html?Name=Media-Info

When submitting a bug or request, please include a test-file or a
patch to an existing test-file that illustrates the bug or desired
feature.

